"0#Quick alignment!|Pam, thank you for seeking alignment on WGD efforts last week with short notice when we faced uncertainty and quickly needed the approval of our VPs to stay on track. We had a very tight deadline to meet and without any hesitation, you got the conversation going and off we went. You‚Äôve been the voice of reason for many years here and we will be sad to see you go and miss your smiling face in the office. I wanted to get this over to you before you go! Thank you and best of luck to you!\n\n1#Thank you for your partnership!|Thank you all for a successful first meeting of the digital advisory committee! All of you shared personal insight and perspective that was extremely valuable in setting the stage for our executive council session. We are extremely excited about how the conversation will continue to grow and evolve moving forward and your voice will be a vital component to shape and maximize our web impact! Thank you all!\n\n2#All the media!|Team - Thank you for an exceptional presentation of your paid media plan today for driving 2H growth and unlocking more opportunity for our company. The image here shows the determination, focus, and careful planning this cross-functional team has put forward. I look forward to refining and finalizing the plan together. Keep up the great work. With gratitude, -C\n\n3#I see you|Pam, I wanted to take a minute to thank you for consistently leading with empathy. I‚Äôm sure it‚Äôs not easy having such a large team, but you always make yourself available and take the time to check-in, to listen if we need an ear, to understand what the struggles are so you can help clear any roadblocks, and to offer advice or constructive feedback when and where needed. It‚Äôs been a crazy year, full of a lot of change, excitement, increased workloads, and shifting priorities - I really appreciate the fact that you have verbally recognized all of this one more than one occasion, that you have related, and have supported and promoted good mental health practices to offset any increased stress. Thanks for your support - I personally have felt seen and heard, and just want you to know that I appreciate it all.\n\n4#Pioneering the Human Workplace|Thank you all for your months-long efforts in creating Workhuman Live Online. Together, you showcased the importance, impact, and transformative power of putting humans at the center of the workplace.    Doing that took the cooperation of teams across Workhuman, including Technology, Product, Workhuman iQ, Sales, Customer Strategy, Customer Service, Finance, Legal, HX, and Marketing. It was a tremendous effort, and in turn, I am immensely proud of what we accomplished.   I know there were difficult moments during the broadcasts, so I want to specifically call out the resolve and focus many of you demonstrated in supporting our customers and prospects with rapid-response access to key content.    While I would say, ‚Äúthat‚Äôs a wrap‚Äù the truth is this is just a beginning‚Äîthe response has been overwhelmingly positive, and I look forward to seeing the impact it has our company‚Äôs growth in the future.   Ultimately, the greatest demonstration of the power of working human is all of you. So again, thank you for the commitment, hard work, and humanity you brought to Workhuman Live Online.    With gratitude, -C\n\n5#Welcome Committee|When I asked if you would help in welcoming my new team member Anna to the Workhuman family, you all stepped right up!! I can‚Äôt thank you enough for taking time out of your busy schedules to have a conversation with Anna on the ins and outs of Workhuman, along with giving her an overview of your roles and how both of our teams connect. Also, my team is so fortunate to have the support from all of you!! I can‚Äôt thank you for the many times that I‚Äôve bothered you (especially at the last minute) to help me craft responses for prospects/customers. Many of my counterparts in the RFP trade don‚Äôt have this level of relationships with SMEs or people within their organizations. My team is very blessed to have you all as partners!!  Thank you for all that you do! Michael\n\n6#You put Spring in my step|Thank you team! I very much appreciate the help, dedication, preparation and execution in the past weeks leading up to today's All Hands. We developed the agenda, built content, created visuals, dealt with final logistics...no matter what the ask, you all dedicated time and energy to deliver and make it seamless. And Aaron, wow - above and beyond to commit and join us from your vacation too!This felt a lot like when we prep for a prospect presentation, so now we wait for the feedback to learn if we were downselected, got VOC or earned the win! üòâ   Thanks again the help ~ I really appreciate the teamwork! (and I'm sure you all appreciate that I didn't continue down my corny path of puns...they don't 'succ'...all I could do not to weave in how y'all were just dandy putting the petal to the metal...)\n\n7#Making it Perfect ! part 2|I forgot to add Pam to this list! I can't thank you all enough for all the time and effort you are putting in to make my life easier. You all are putting so much time in and racking your brain in how to fix my Dashboard and redirect leads and MQL's . I really appreciate everything you do for me to make my life easier and so I can make better use of my time and be more useful to my team so they can get more meetings and close more deals!\n\n8#Operating with Excellence and Agility|Pam - Outstanding job bringing Jason, Steve C, me, and the rest of the Sales Ops and Finance team through our first Marketing Ops review today. The materials were well thought out and the discussion was exceptionally well facilitated. You've brought forward a new discipline around top of funnel management that collectively I know is highly valued across these stakeholders. As a result of your leadership we have an enhanced level of awareness for which levers to pull and when. And you've established this as an important forum we'll use to manage the business. Our plans will always be dynamic, and we'll never get it exactly right on the first pass - you've effectively acknowledged this and have created pathways for dialogue and an ongoing planning with our partners that ensure we're taking an agile approach to top of funnel goals. With gratitude, -C\n\n9#Nine Years Going Strong|It all started back in 2012!  It's wild to think of the changes the 3 of us have seen over the last 9 years at Workhuman.  Looking back, the two of you have always there.  From day one I knew if I needed anything - from support, advice, a laugh or even just a kick in the @$$ - I could turn to Pam or Mark.  Your leadership has shaped me in so many ways.  Thank you both for always being my constant.  Let's go another nine years together!\n\n10#Special Edition Team Meeting|Pam, thank you for hosting an **employee appreciation day special edition** of our team meeting today! I haven‚Äôt laughed like that at work in a while, and it was a much needed respite from the craziness of our day-to-day. I really appreciate the time and thought you put into the whole thing. The team jeopardy game was a hoot (I‚Äôm still dying from the John Cena reference) and the cupcakes were such a thoughtful gesture (especially since you custom ordered them for each of us based on our individual likes!). Thank you for taking the time to organize this for the team and for recognizing that we could all use a break from the daily grind. Laughter is food for the soul and it was much appreciated!\n\n11#Creative discussion partners!|Team, thank you for your participation, creative discussion and investment in our process of defining Marketing KPIs as we envision our plan for development. I was inspired and motivated by your expertise and feedback during our session yesterday. This has truly been a team effort held up by all humans involved! I'm excited to see where our imagination and determination take marketing analytics.\n\n12#ABM Mythbusters|Pam / Krista,  Thank you, both, for spending additional time to brainstorm and talk through the challenges, structure and potential solutions for the ABM team and its future.  The ever-thought provoking balance between field marketing and ABM each play a vital role in lead gen and pipeline support.    I truly appreciate your on-going collaboration as we continue to evolve the team towards greatness!\n\n13#Forecasting 2021|Pam,  fantastic job presenting the MQL Forecast for 2021.   You have put so much work and strategic planning into 2021 and it was great to see the excitement about the future for all those efforts.  MQL's are an important part of the entire business and you laid out the foundation for what will be a great year.  Thanks for all you do and I look forward to seeing it all unfold!\n\n14#13,000 MQLs? ... by when?!|Team - Outstanding presentation today with Steve, Jason and myself regarding a disciplined and proactive projection of MQLs by quarter and program. This represents a new high water mark of organization, data-driven insights, and focus being brought to our joint sales and marketing planning and execution process. Thank you for standing up a framework that will become the bedrock of subsequent monthly operational reviews. Your focus on results through careful planning and accountability comes through clearly. With gratitude, -C\n\n15#Crushin' the (sales) calendar|Team - outstanding job organizing and communicating our plan and schedule of joint sales and marketing campaigns for Q1. The level of coordination and detail was very well received on the SLT call this week. Success is connected to exceptional execution of a shared plan. I believe we are in great position for this as evidenced by the ramp up in registrations for our upcoming customer webinar. Well done. With gratitude, -C\n\n16#Marketer or Marketeer?|No matter which way you market yourself, Amy and I wanted to thank this entire team for the investment over the last few weeks, leading up to today - our first integrated planning offsite of 2021! You invested your time, energy, mind and heart in the offsite topics and each other. We appreciate the opportunity for transparency, communication and idea sharing around two of our most important upcoming initiatives between the Brand Relaunch and WH Live. We're both excited to be aligned, looking forward to building out integrated marketing plans together, and thrilled to be on this journey with each of you. Onward we go! Z & Amy\n\n17#Improving communications between Marketing & Sales|Pam I want to thank you for showing great urgency on an action to help align the sales and marketing teams today. This morning I mentioned it would be valuable to have a visible place for the sales team to access the marketing calendar. Before the day was over you had it placed on Seismic so everyone can get access. Thank you!\n\n18#Zoom, zoom, zoom around with me!|Tim, Camila, Doug, Pam, Michelle, Donna-Louise and Olga, it was such a pleasure meeting you all on our zoom around this week! I loved how each of you were so real, so authentic and openly shared your joys during the pandemic. I know i certainly learned a lot about each of you in such a short amount of time together and am can't wait to learn more. You are fascinating humans; juggling families, new homes, co-working with significant others, and balancing work/life during these crazy times. I'm in awe of each of you and I really am looking forward to catching up in person one day for that hug. ü§ó\n\n19#New Year Goals|Thank you all for providing your feedback on the speakers bureau as we closed out 2020. This recognition is long overdue (holiday brain) but it was extremely helpful to hear your goals for the new year to better understand how the bureau can support upcoming projects with speaking engagements. Whether you walked us through a planning deck, sent notes via email, or participated in an open dialogue - it all helped to shape our ‚Äò21 planning efforts.\n\n20#Westward Bound|Team, I just wanted to take a moment to acknowledge the great work and quick decision-making that has been happening with the West Coast campaign. I really appreciate all that has been done. This moment comes off the back of a great creative review that happened yesterday, where we were able to collaborate on feedback and expectations, all while reviewing the first creative test run of our refreshed look. There's a million reasons this all could have gotten derailed, and it hasn't. We're SO CLOSE to it being live and out the door, and I really just want to take a moment to appreciate what we are accomplishing as a group. Dianne for driving and keeping us on target; Laura and Pam for the direction and productive feedback; Katie and Dario for your feedback and eye for best practices; Lauren our wordsmith; and Alana, for your patience, diligence, and creative effort bringing it all together in a fresh new look, while having to build in an unfamiliar platform, with new types of deliverables... Guys, this is the type of collaboration that will really take us to a new level. Looking forward to launch :)\n\n21#Raising the Bar|On behalf of Chris and myself, we wanted to shout from the roof tops about what a great job you did with the vendor strategy for Demand Generation and engagement management technology.  You put in place a solid process of due diligence that included a strong panel of key stakeholders.  Your careful decision consideration criteria and recommendation process has elevated and will accelerate our ability to reach and engage ICPs historically out of reach or out of sight.  You made the decision to work with 6sense an easy one...not to mention that we will enhance TCO.  Here's to raising the bar!!!\n\n22#Fresh thinking|Pam and Devin, thank you so much for a great discussion on how to best up-level our webinars moving forward. Pam, we‚Äôve had a lot of success to date but one never gets ahead by standing still and I appreciate you pushing the team and I to always be looking ahead, to be innovative and think outside the box. Devin, your fresh perspective is much appreciated! You‚Äôre a treasure trove of great ideas and I really appreciate you allowing us to pick your brain for an hour. I‚Äôm looking forward to working with you more in the future and am grateful for the opportunity to learn from you. I‚Äôm also super excited to explore the ideas we discussed and put them into practice. There‚Äôs no question that they will only serve to enrich the experience for registrants and attendees alike and up-level our webinar game. Thank you both!\n\n23#But you \"made it work\" in 2020!|Team - Tim Gunn was right! We had very ambitious plans for 2020! And then they all changed to a \"different set\" of \"very ambitious\" endeavors and goals ... and you thrived, moved the organization forward to growth, and made sure businesses knew what's next, started now! Thank you for major contributions like: Implementing a data-driven approach to lead generation and pipeline growth resulting in significant growth of MQLs to 10,000!; Launching our first-ever TV and OTT ads; Helping executives unlock grand gestures of gratitude through Team Awards; Developing and delivering two WHLs (albeit in very different ways than originally planned); And helping grow our Employee Experience to rank on the Great Places to Work in 2020! Way to rock it out in 2020, and show 2021 a preview of what a human centered, impact driven approach looks like. Thank you for a terrific year of results, teamwork, support of our stakeholder partners, and resiliency through and through. With gratitude, -C\n\n24#On Wednesdays, We Meet, We Talk, We Think, We Act.|And then we do it all over again the following week. I am grateful for your commitment to our Marketing Leadership call week in and week out. Sure, we might not have 52 weeks on the books for 2020, but we MOST DEFINITELY have twice that many hours and then some between our regular weekly meetings and our virtual offsite time together. Focus group of 1 here, but I find the time we spend together immensely valuable - hearing about what various teams are working on, gathering different points of view, discussing ways we can work better together, learning from each of you as subject matter experts and awesome marketers and humans...and last but not least, strengthening the connections between us even though we have been working apart since the early days of March. Enjoy a couple weeks off and we'll assemble again before you know it! THANK YOU!\n\n25#Winner, Winner ... Turkey Dinner?!|Kristen, Kelsey, Pam - Congratulations on your \"win\" as determined by a selection of your Customer Marketing peers in the first-ever, inaugural, \"Design Your Own Turkey Headband\". It was a hotly contested and spirited competition that will surely become a favorite tradition! Well done and with gratitude, -C\n\n26#Company Overview Document|Ilana & Pam - thank you both for your support over the past week to help create a document that did not exist last week. We needed a quick one or two page document that helps tell our story. What we had did not capture what was needed. Both of you jumped on this and a few days later developed a great document. Thank you both for the urgency to help get this produced.\n\n27#2021 Marketing Planning Pros!|So, we didn‚Äôt quite spend 6 hours together today but pretty close to it! Add in previous working sessions, the pre-work PLUS the work to come, and we will easily surpass that. BUT in the end, we'll be poised and ready to execute a solid plan for the new year. We appreciate your commitment to the 2021 marketing planning process. We‚Äôre taking a different approach this year and we‚Äôre coming close to the 10-month mark of working remotely during an epic year of CRAZY. With so many players involved, different points of view, and known foundational gaps like solid messaging ‚Äì (YES, we know, we know!)‚Ä¶it‚Äôs not an easy task. We are optimistic about the progress we‚Äôre making together. We are grateful for your focus on the end goal and how we'll get there. Thank you for partnering with us to sharpen our strategies and set our teams up to properly support the business in 2021. Onward we go! Z + Amy\n\n28#Utilizing Your Network|Pam, Alex Paz and myself wanted to thank you for connecting us with your contact at Boston Scientific. We just got off a call with him and he gave us some great information and is helping to connect us with a colleague in HR. Thank you so much for your willingness to help!\n\n29#Congrats Workhuman Live Team!|Team ‚Äì A HUGE shout out to each of you for helping deliver a fantastic event yesterday. It truly was amazing! Your hard work and dedication to excellence have set a NEW example for everyone in our organization. I‚Äôm inspired by the ingenuity and creativity of everyone‚Äôs contribution ‚Äì planning, marketing, storytelling, vendor management, customer support, technical execution, and so much more. Your efforts have allowed us to create a new conversation in the marketplace. I‚Äôm genuinely excited to build on this shared momentum to help every organization bring people closer together. None of this would be possible without YOU. I extend my heartiest congratulations on achieving a fantastic milestone. Well done ALL!\n\n30#these are my people|This award is incredibly overdue for my people; and I apologize if this feels impersonal as one gratitude moment, but I need these humans to know (LIKE, NOW) how much I appreciate them.  The last couple of months have been by far the most challenging I've experienced in my professional life.  Don't tell IT but this laptop may have flown across the room a time or two! (Hey.. maybe that's why my speakers don't work??)  But I have to remind myself, we're doing big things.  The excitement I have in Workhuman, and all of it's fast-paced, innovative goodness, far exceeds the hard days.  And you know what else knocks the stress on it's ass?  YOU.  Each one of you have played a pivotal role in the growth of this organization, team and myself.  Your impact is beyond words; they wouldn't even do my appreciation justice.  Please a moment this weekend to think about how great you are; how hard you work; and how much better you make my world.  Thank you Andy.  Thank you Chris.  Thank you Miguel.  Thank you Kristie.  Thank you Mark.  Thank you Jason.  Thank you Anthony.  Thank you Krista.  Thank you Erik.  Thank you Pam.\n\n31#Offsite virtually, but totally productive day IRL!|Team ‚Äì Thank you for your active participation in our 2nd planning ‚Äúvirtual‚Äù offsite. The energy level was high and the level of engagement and strategic thinking was strong. Patti and I are excited about the united approach to not only long-term marketing planning, but building a strong culture for the entire Marketing team where different points of view are embraced and we are continually testing new ways of working to optimize our contributions to overall business results. I‚Äôm genuinely excited to build on this shared momentum to bring our 2021 plans to life. With gratitude ‚Äì C.\n\n32#üôåüèª Upleveling our Team Updates üôåüèª|Week in and week out, each of you contribute to a few different communication vehicles we have to keep our team and stakeholders across the company up to date on all the amazing things that are happening in the world of Marketing. About a month or so ago, I came to the team with a new process for pulling together our weekly updates and challenged each of us to think about the intended audience and what would be most valuable to them...We started including more metrics and other performance data in our look-backs and introduced headlines to provide more focus. We are also incorporating more visuals to keep the content fresh and engaging. We held each other accountable to sticking to a standard template and hitting deadlines so that we could get the updates edited and out the door in a timely fashion. I know between the weekly marketing updates, the digital programming status reports and ELT progress updates, you probably feel like this is communication overload at times, but they are important in staying connected and current especially when we are all remote. I sincerely appreciate your part in helping to improve the quality. THANK YOU!\n\n33#Moving Moments|Thank you all for playing an integral role in our Change Management workshop to work through how to effectively roll out DG 2.0 to sales. Your input will help inform the strategy and ensures we are taking your day-to-day processes into account when working through all of these new initiatives. Thank you again for dedicating a few hours of your day to this discussion and ensuring a solid partnership between marketing and sales.\n\n34#Marketing Calendar & Focus on Results|Pam I want to thank you for the extra hard work you have done over the past 60 days as we built out our marketing plans for Q3 and Q4. You not only shaped our strategy you are in every day help ensure we drive the metrics needed on MQL and pipeline for us to reach out goals. Thank you!\n\n35#2nd half marketing plan - Drive 4 RQ pipeline|Chris & Pam thank you for the efforts over the past several months to map out a marketing plan designed to help us drive our MQL's and 4 RQ pipeline. Several key events for the team to leverage. The combo of account focus (ICP) and events offers a strong pathway to success. Look forward to the continued focus on hitting all of our pipeline targets.\n\n36#Virtual Offsite - but 100% Productive IRL|Team - On behalf of Patti and myself thank you for a tremendous Q3 strategic planning and execution offsite last week. Both presenters and discussion partners excelled in their roles to communicate and strengthen existing plans. Your engagement and participation was locked in for the full session. And it's exciting to see this team rally around a new way of working that is oriented toward connecting business results to the strategic objectives of all our 2H initiatives within Marketing and across partner stakeholder teams. Thanks for leaning into the process - it's becoming a difference maker for us and helping us cut through our own noise! -C\n\n37#Guiding Light!|Not the soap opera! Thank you for all your support last week through the H2 planning process. From sharing your insights and perspectives on our Tuesday presentations to helping me navigate and complete the H2 brief for my program during our Friday call - your unwavering support gave me the strength I needed to push through and make it all come together. You also shared feedback on Evanta in a timely manner for me to share with them so that we could quickly act to re-imagine our sponsorship in creative ways that fit our business needs. I appreciate your attention to the needs at hand, and being available to answer my questions and concerns and provide feedback and share insights to keep work progressing forward. Thanks for all of your much needed support!\n\n38#Collaboration at it‚Äôs Finest|Thank you all for being so invested in the Demand Gen 2.0 project. From the start, you have helped marketing define lead scoring, create sales plays, and define our Tier 1 account list - which will ultimately accelerate deals. We genuinely appreciate your dedication to this new process. This wouldn‚Äôt be successful without your invaluable insights, questions, and partnership. We look forward to continuing to work together to evolve our marketing and sales strategy!\n\n39#Welcoming to the Team|Pam, thank you so much for all you have done to include Dario and I into your team! I was skeptical of a new daily meeting, but it REALLY works. I feel more connected to teammates during these last few weeks than I have for months. I am so happy to continue my Workhuman journey under your leadership.\n\n40#Allow me to introduce our 6th team member ... \"Mo\"|As in \"Mo\"-mentum ... Team, great series of discussions, debate, and innovative thinking being brought to our 2H planning through the last 3 weeks of collaborative planning sessions! Excited to see we're wrestling the plan to ground with a mix of data, curiosity and grit! ... Biggest pipeline ever here we come!! With gratitude, -C\n\n41#Thank you!|Pam - I want to thank you for all your support over these last few months. These are trying times, but your mentorship and ability to navigate through challenges have been incredibly helpful. I look forward to being able to connect with you every month. It is refreshing to be able to have discussions with you about the future of the business, or what we can double down on for ABM to help the teams work together. Thank you for being a great teammate!\n\n42#The power of indirect influence at State Street|Pam, I want to thank you for your indirect influence on a major stakeholder in State Street's implementation of WH. Your friend Nikki while not part of the direct decision making group undoubtedly has a tremendous amount of influence and a strong voice in the direction they take moving forward.  Her level of engagement has been very high and it almost as if she was brain washed a little going in using our talk track and being an advocate of what we're trying to do for companies.  When our sales team reaches out to those in non-sales roles asking for help this is a perfect example of how engaging with a non-decision maker can be helpful to the business!  THANK YOU!\n\n43#Putting the A+ in Alignment Session|Team - thank you for an outstanding call today that unlocked great alignment on near term initiatives and opened the door to exciting future business opportunity topics we‚Äôll tackle together. Wanted to recognize the productivity of our call, partnership and open mindedness demonstrated. With gratitude, -C\n\n44#Leadership|Pam - I want to say how thankful I am for our working relationship always, but especially lately. I feel like we're in sync on initiatives and I'm very impressed by your leadership and input on various projects. You've taken on a larger team, remotely, and have managed to keep us all connected, engaged, and focused. This can be a hard task to navigate while managing all of your own initiatives - which we know are a lot right now! Thanks for being a wonderful mentor and leader throughout it all!\n\n45#Putting the \"Lift off\" in \"Kick off\"|Team - as workplaces everywhere contemplate the next phase of work, we are leading the way in what that looks like externally and with our customers. It also means we need to evolve internally. I was so impressed by the team work and open mindedness demonstrated by this cross-functional group in today's kick off! So, as they say, \"Houston, we have lift off!\" Excited to see where this group takes the next phase of what it means to thrive and workhuman. With gratitude, -C\n\n46#Fast help for team|Pam wanted to say thank for your quick follow up to support a key executive demo next week. Within minutes of the request you had help secure the support needed. Thank you!\n\n47#Setting our team up for success!|Pam, you truly set all of us all up for success with WHL follow-up strategy. You kept us well informed, aligned and doing the best work we can. We couldn't have brought all of it together without you. Even with all of the quick turns and pivots, you kept our team marching to the same goal and the collaboration was flowing so freely. Thanks again for leading us and getting us to the finish line!!\n\n48#Keeping Humanity Alive with Live!|Team ‚Äì Thank you for delivering a high quality, compelling, on brand, and ‚Äúof the moment‚Äù digital event. In less than six weeks you expertly pivoted from the cancellation of our physical events in San Antonio and Dublin and leaped into bold new thinking that resulted in our Workhuman Live Stream event. You were fearless in pursuit of our audacious goal of 10,000 registrants and charged furiously at it ‚Äì obliterating the goal and achieving more than 15,000+ registrants. This level of success took thoughtful planning, decisive and quick action, creativity, and relentless outreach to secure exceptional guest speakers, high profile customer stories, and new sponsorships. There was clear demonstration of teamwork, resilience, grit ‚Äì and quite a bit of ‚Äúgood cheer‚Äù across this group. It was an example of Workhuman at our best. This is a significant achievement in the company‚Äôs history and will continue to pay dividends in the following areas: Social reach; The launch of our new products like Moodtracker; Deepening existing customer relationships; Establishing strong new footholds with future customers; And growing profitably. My hat‚Äôs off to you all ‚Äì when Humanity needed us most ‚Äì you all rallied to give Humanity the company it needed now more than ever. On behalf of the Leadership Team and myself, Thank you - Eric\n\n49#Detailed Plan for Marketing Success|Would like to take this opportunity to thank Pam for showing great urgency as we detail the marketing follow up for our events. We had a call on Monday and discussed the need for a more detailed plan. By Tuesday morning Pam had a solid plan in place. Thank you Pam for your dedication and follow up to ensure we capitalize on our events.\n\n50#Spotlight Speaker Success Stories|Team - thank you for stepping into the spotlight during our last three marketing town halls. You‚Äôve shown at an exemplary level of innovation, determination, and grit amidst our new normal. You‚Äôve conveyed your success stories (Merck webinar, Keeping work human series, and WHL) with an awesome combination of humility and accessibility. Thank you, thank you, thank you for being leaders of the moment and in the moment. The best practices you‚Äôve shared and modeled to achieve such high levels of success are great guideposts and shining examples of a high performing culture ! Well done and with gratitude, -C\n\n51#Wait! Was that really only 90 days?!|Team - Thank you for making this next phase of our journey and evolution together as a team so successful! Lets just say the first 60 day together were much different than our last 30 days together(ish)! Wanted to celebrate all we‚Äôve done together in our first 3 months as a team. Attached is my quick recap and where I see us delivering results in Q2. Thank you, I‚Äôm truly appreciative of all you do!  With gratitude, -C\n\n52#To the team that \"broke\" SHRM.com! ...|Team - First thank you for your OUTSTANDING work on the concept, design, and run up to the Merck+SHRM webinar! This is going to be so successful because the content is OF THE MOMENT RELEVANT and it's being told through the lens of what a real-life customer is doing RIGHT NOW to lean in to  recognition amidst crisis-laden uncertain times. I am so proud of the alignment and partnership you've demonstrated with our entire Sales and CS organizations - TREMENDOUS teamwork! In less than four weeks you've taken an idea, pivoted and evolved content to match the market where it's at, secure a key customer, successfully execute our highest-ever webinar registration count, and partner with SHRM, another thought leader in our industry ... that alone is a massively high bar ... but response was so strong, this campaign overwhelmed SHRM.com's technology and we had to cap registration at 3,200 ... you turned what could be a \" :( face\"  moment around by innovating and proactively communication solutions to our Sales and CS leaders. You all are a FORCE to be reckoned with, and have fueled our brand and our mission greatly by showing what success looks like. I am honored to work alongside such a talented, agile, and forward-looking group of marketeers. So, yeah, I guess you could say, you're a big deal! ... Well done! With gratitude, -C\n\n53#Thank you for Daring Greatly|Pam, I wanted to sincerely thank you for your understanding, guidance, open communication and caring in the midst of all the uncertainty and challenges that we‚Äôre faced with. I really appreciate you holding true to your commitment to keep the team informed ‚Äì our quick daily check-ins as a team have been super helpful (and have also provided a daily dose of laughter). I know things are moving at a rapid pace, so it‚Äôs nice to feel that we‚Äôre kept in the loop on the latest initiatives and updates across the board. What‚Äôs really stood out to me however is how you always start the meeting asking, very sincerely, how everyone is doing. You‚Äôve been super honest, very open, and at times even vulnerable by sharing personal stories or personal feelings in the midst of everything going on. By doing so, you‚Äôve established a higher level of trust, and I am very grateful to have such an empathetic leader for our team. Thank you for the open communication, for always checking-in, and for all the wonderful advice and guidance you‚Äôve given me.\n\n54#Thankful|I wanted to take a moment and say how thankful I am for this team. Ever since Demand Gen and Field Marketing joined one team, we're communicating and collaborating more than ever. Everyone on this team brings a unique skill set and is more than willing to offer their expertise on any project. Each member of this team is humble, but yet, a rock star.   Laura - Your execution and thoughtfulness on projects is so impressive.  Jeff - Your eagerness to jump right into projects is really standing out.  Diane - You're quiet, but mighty. You always ask the right questions and think of every detail. Mark - I really appreciate the insight you bring to every project and the constant collaboration. Pam - Your leadership and consistent communication with the team has made this difficult time much easier.  Ryan - I'm always amazed with the projects you work on and the detail you put into them. Stacey - Thanks for stepping up and helping support Field Marketing during a time when it is needed.  Thanks team, I appreciate you all!\n\n55#Webinar Tenacity!|Laura, Pam, and Jess, I have been totally impressed by the focus you have put into the upcoming Webinar and the tenacity you have exhibited in making sure we get everything we need.  From securing a great client, to pivoting on the fly the topic to be more relevant to these challenging times, to getting our partner to share info with us that they normally don't, to making sure we have all that info in our systems and communicated out to the company, you have done it all with a great spirit of teamwork.  Thank you all for all you do and I can't wait to see what comes of it!!!\n\n56#Best. Team. Ever.|Thank you for a great Zoom meeting to align around our short term priorities while daring to dream and proactively plan for longer term priorities. Not an easy task to do when the \"here and now\" is all anyone of us can think about lately. I was so impressed with everyone's willingness to think about team resources in a different way and also our shared commitment to the good work and strategic thinking that we already did together pre COVID-19 crisis. This was my most productive meeting of the day and an awesome way to end the week. I am grateful for this awesome team. Thank you!\n\n57#Just a little Patience....|Guns and Roses, right?! Just a little Patience!!!! I wanted to thank the team for quick help, guidance, and yes, PATIENCE while we sorted our strategy for the Merck upcoming webinar. With many moving parts and things not being as straight forward as normal, I very much appreciate the teams willingness to help take a step back and inform the team and keep us in in check with the direction and the good work that has taken place to build the content! Thanks for being such great team mates!\n\n58#CSR Committee|A heartfelt note of gratitude for your overwhelming and immediate support of our CSR initiative. In the midst of all that is unfolding across the company as we respond to COVID-19, you found the time to join our little committee and came up with several outstanding ideas in no time at all! We are rallying around those ideas and from it will emerge a short and long-term plan to further our impact on lives and communities. Onward and forward!\n\n59#Helping Excellence Become A Reality|Along with Rosette and the team (Omar, Naomi, Amanda and Krista) we would like to thank this amazing group of colleagues who joined us with little notice to be the Alpha Testers  of a new workshop we have created for prospects and maybe even customers ‚Äì  Keeping Work Human.  Like the judges on America‚Äôs Got Talent, you silently sat then gave your direct, candid review verbally (and then used Conversations to deliver the feedback in writing).   You shared your collective wisdom, gave us thoughts on how to improve and then hit the gold button - so next stop is to take the show on the road.  Off to TX we (virtually) go to deliver this to USAA and there is a potential of General Mills in Minnesota next and maybe even Memorial Hermann Health System  Rosette and all of us that worked many hours on this workshop  appreciate you all so much for jumping with little notice and helping us all prepare to deliver excellence.\n\n60#Well that was NOT in my 30/60/90 day plan! ...|Team - A quick thank you to celebrate being 60 days in together. You continue to adapt to the businesses needs and lead through uncertain times with a high demonstrated commitment to the priorities we've aligned on to grow the business - ie., Build the brand; Acquire new customer; Grow existing customers; and Build our culture through people. Although COVID was in NO ONE'S playbook, you rallied and risen to this new challenge by partnering with me on a slightly \"revised\" version of my 30/60/90 plan. This is having such a positive halo effect on our teams. Look forward to the next 30 days of the plan ... whatever that looks, and with confidence that if we need to write it 1 page, 1 day at a time - this is the team I'm excited to do it with. Stay healthy, human, and connected! With gratitude, -C\n\n61#Always being there!|Pam, thank you for joining our BDR team meetings to keep us up on any new marketing initiatives/content/developments/campaigns/ideas/etc! You have always been an a tremendous partner with sales and thank you for helping us stay connected during this time.\n\n62#Making COVID Connections for Merck|While we're still in the process of creating a webinar for Merck, I had to pause and appreciate the amount of effort that has gone into creating an exceptional experience and one that ties into the current pandemic situation. In the span of the week, we've pivoted and changed the focus of the webinar altogether to be timely, considerate and ties into concerns of the greater HR community, while also being in line with the vision that our contacts at Merck have. That includes multiple revisions of content, shepherding and managing approvals of interested parties. Not to mention creating a final piece that will speak to the strong partnership we have with Merck, as well as the human messaging we want to have in the market. Despite the constant changes, I walk away from of all of our brainstorming sessions feeling energized and excited at the story we are weaving, supplemented by WARI data. Thank you all for the talent, commitment and passion you have brought and continue bringing to this effort.\n\n63#Delivering the Human Touch|When the COVID-19 pandemic began to accelerate, our marketing instinct immediately went to providing a human face on our content. There is no more powerful thought leadership than humans speaking with humans ‚Äì sharing experiences, emotions, and best practices on how best to craft a path forward in these unprecedented times. That was the inspiration for the daily video series, ‚ÄúKeeping Work Human,‚Äù which launched last week amid the flurry of everything else we are working on. James and Matt ‚Äì you stepped up and deftly handled the logistics of turning a Zoom video conference call into usable, shareable video. Pam ‚Äì you project-managed the overall logistics, setting up the invites, and showing agility when we had to pivot. Amy ‚Äì you immediately energized your team to schedule guest speakers. Mike ‚Äì you were at the ready to transition the videos to Workhuman Radio podcasts. Sarah and Jess ‚Äì you stepped up to write the question frameworks and provide a content resource. John and Diane ‚Äì you saw what was happening and introduced better discipline and process. Jen ‚Äì you were our first guest and dazzled our viewers with unique leadership best practices to manage remote teams. And Steve ‚Äì our host ‚Äì your ability to set the tone, and keep our guests at ease with your authenticity and humble heart, is what makes it all work. We‚Äôve only just begun ‚Äì and we have a busy few weeks ahead ‚Äì but I couldn‚Äôt be prouder of this team and the messaging we are bringing to market.\n\n64#Sharing is caring|High 5s to you 5 fine humans! Why you ask? I pulled together a marketplace update over the weekend but with more than a dozen companies to track, I knew I could not do it alone. I asked the marketing leaders who could help out and Dan and John - you both didn't blink raising your hand to chip in. Dan - your team is cranking out thoughtful content every day but you generously offered to let Jess H help with this. John - first you said you could ask your team to help but then you decided to take on the extra workload yourself! Jess - you were quick, thorough and proactively reached out to me with your specific updates throughout the week. But, as the week went on and our COVID related scope of work kept growing, I knew I had to reassess how we resourced the efforts so that we could provide timely updates to Sales and the entire organization. Pam - I went to you next and asked if I could enlist Mark's help. And you too, didn't hesitate a second. You quickly talked to Mark and followed up to tell me he'd be in touch. Within hours, Mark not only proactively reached out to me for the download but he took the project on with ease and enthusiasm and delivered a new update of today's marketplace COVID related activity Hugely valuable. Thank you all! I love this team and this great example of teamwork at its finest.\n\n65#Is it still Wednesday?|Team -  First, thank you - often and always.  Second, I want to acknowledge we are operating in unprecedented times. This can trigger feelings of discomfort and anxiety if you let it. But, I believe we are strong enough together to rally, support, and mobilize each other to overcome that potential because you all as leaders already have. Know that every moment of progress you‚Äôve made this week already illustrates your strength, determination, and grit.  In the broader context - none of us are guaranteed a tomorrow - COVID may exacerbate that mindset - but in reality this too shall pass and we all will be stronger from it - personally and professionally.  I believe in you. And I believe in us together. Our collective strengths to overcome and our true human spirit to persevere will best this.  I am honored to serve alongside you in the pursuit of our brand, our customers, and the greater community we serve.  Thank you for all your support, kindness, and compassion you've extended to me this week!  With gratitude, -C\n\n66#It's Go Time!|Team - I wanted to first say thank you for your rapid response to the business's need for a COVID rapid response campaign. I also want to acknowledge that working at this pace and with a level of uncertainty may be new and/or uncomfortable, but that has not stopped this group from leaping into action, mobilizing, and being agile and responsive to rapidly evolving priorities - including stopping existing work, pivoting planned content, and being open-minded about new ways of working team together and team apart (as we leverage remote technology for the next while). Still lots to do, and I'm confident with the cohesion demonstrated this week we will do great things that help our current and future customers navigate uncertain times and that we will unlock new approaches and agility as a cross functional team. Thank you all. With gratitude, -C\n\n67#First Class Collaboration|Team! I wanted to say congratulations and celebrate the collaboration that infused our FY20 Marketing Strategy Board. As of this past Friday we have an aligned, crisp, and clear plan for Marketing's focus and KPIs that sits perfectly between the Company's goals, objectives, and major priorities. I also want to recognize the diligence that went into to making this be a plan that effectively spans Customer + Brand Marketing and reflects alignment with our key partners (SLT, CS, CX, and Finance). It is metrics driven to ensure accountability and through it's more streamlined nature, now infinitely more shareable with our teams and partners. Look forward to rolling this out to the teams through all hands these next two weeks and continuing to revisit it for focus, alignment, and relevance to the business's needs as our business evolves. Love to see the positive momentum and teamwork modeled to produce this output - lets keep it going. With gratitude, -C\n\n68#Quick Thinking!|Pam - thank you so much for thinking of reaching back out to Jeff when it came to kicking off and hiring for Jill's open coordinator position. Because of you, he was able to be given a fair shot at a role that seems as though it was made for him, and now he gets to be a part of the Workhuman family! This is such a win not only for Jeff as a candidate, but for us as an organization!\n\n69#November 21, 2019|Assuming Outlook is accurate, November 21, 2019  was our first official \"Marketing Directors meeting.\" Sixteen weeks later, I wanted to take a moment to personally thank each of you for ALLLL the time and energy you've invested in our time together. We've been meeting on a weekly basis  to establish more visibility, create more alignment across functional teams, collaborate on short and long term planning, negotiate budgets, brainstorm core marketing themes, discuss better ways of working together...the list goes on an on. And while I know we all cringe at the thought of another meeting on our calendars when we are starved for time, I strongly believe if we come together on a regular basis and focus on the right things, we'll all be smarter for it. I have so much gratitude for each of you! Thank you and see you next Wednesday!\n\n70#Feeling connected|Pam and Jill - I wanted to say thank you for the warm welcome you've both provided to me as I made the move into the Customer Marketing team this quarter. Not only do I feel a personal connection strengthening between us, I feel our work is becoming more and more connected which is exactly part of our vision! You've both been proactively bringing me into various discussions and meetings and totally receptive to my ideas. As you know, Eric B and I often joked that we were often forgotten in our previous Product Marketing roles. There was some truth behind the joking. We had each other but I never truly felt like part of a team and now, I do - thanks in large part to you both! I hope you agree that we are getting into a good groove and are happy about the progress we're making on our strategic marketing plan. I am very excited to partner with you and the rest of our group to bring the plan to life and accomplish amazing things together this year. Go Team!!\n\n71#Best First 30 Days Ever!|Team - I was reflecting on how much we've accomplished during our first month together. I selected Urgency for this note because it best reflects what all of you have demonstrated - ie., the asap tackling of tough challenges with a sense of Shoshin (ÂàùÂøÉ) a word from Zen Buddhism meaning \"beginner's mind.\" To me this means displaying an attitude of openness, eagerness, and lack of preconceptions when studying a subject, even when studying at an advanced level, just as a beginner would. This truly captures the dynamic we've co-built and are accelerating progress in. A quick recap of five significant things we've accomplished together: 1.) Alignment with cross functional partners (SLT, CS/CX, and MLT); 2.) Re-organizing to achieve FY20 priorities and accelerate growth; 3.) Moving the needle toward stronger, crisper, more provocative marketing messages; 4.) As leaders, together, building a shared model of transparency, trust, and robust debate; and 5.) Leveling up to strategic joint business planning. In ways big and small you have made me feel welcome, informed, and more self-aware of how to build a successful team. Jill from our dine around and leadership on Demand 2.0, to Pam with your advice on language for positioning the re-org, to Jeff from your \"get it done and here's what I need from you clarity\" on all things WHL audience acquisition and shared love of sarcasm, to Z your willingness to be the glue between teams and dedicate source for Girl Scout cookies - I want to say thank you for all we've done together and a \"save\" a future thank you for all we will do together. Happy Friday to all - keep up the great human work - it matters. With gratitude, -C\n\n72#People-First Leadership|Team - I wanted to recognize the effort that went into our recent Customer Marketing re-alignment. Driven by and reflective of your input and support we implemented changes that were perceived positively by the business, and by - putting people first and considering the human aspects involved in change - have been received positively as growth and on-strategy changes by the great humans that make up the Customer Marketing organization. I thought it was important to celebrate this moment, because change is often scary, especially for teams in flux - but your advice and guidance around putting people first (always) directly influenced a plan that was highly communicative, well-scheduled, and well-executed by all involved. We are well on our way to the modernization of our Customer Marketing function. Thank you for building strong relationships on this journey - I'm optimistic they will pay dividends throughout FY20 and beyond! With gratitude, -C\n\n73#PUMPED!!! About Partnership ...|Jill, Pam - Thank you for your leadership on our Marketing Calendar Alignment workshop with SLT, CS, and CX Leaders today. This moment mattered today and will pay dividends continuously in FY20. I want to specifically recognize a thoughtful, well-prepared set of meeting materials and discussion guide. It generated a high level of engagement and participation from our partners, and created the basis for a strong go-forward platform for iterating, evolving, and delivering a dynamic Marketing plan that is on strategy, aligned with our sellers' and customers' needs, and explicitly linked to our business goals. It also reflected critical transparency and collaboration dynamics we are building cross-functionally. Thank you, well done, and excited about the momentum we have going. With gratitude, -C\n\n74#Value Based Webinar Events|Thank you Chris & Pam for your partnership to help launch a value based webinar series! We have amazing customers who are getting tremendous value from our solution. Appreciate how you have teamed up with us on shaping and getting this underway.\n\n75#Project Bow Tie|Pam, Jill and Matt, I just wanted to call out the wonderful job you are doing with Project Bow Tie.  Reimagining our demand generation function is daunting.  But you managed Phase 1 so smoothly and we're starting to build some real momentum now.  Not only have you navigated through those ideal customer elements seamlessly, but you have kept all stakeholders well involved, informed and excited.  This type of innovation that brings together cross-functional teams and gets them all pulling in the same direction is a great example for how we will all have to act in the coming years to continue the company's growth and innovation.  We still have a long way to go but well done so far!\n\n76#Trying Something Different!|Amazing demand and field team, wanted to take a moment to say a huge thank you for spending a few hours after a busy holiday season to try something different! Rather than just running through a traditional planning process complete with PPT slides and grids; you all immersed yourselves in something uncommon; roasts and toasts, sticky notes (big and small!) and breaking into teams (outside of your own 'lane') - hackathon style! So happy to see such amazing ideas free-flowing, tremendous collaboration and the willingness to try something completely out of the ordinary and be SUPER engaged during it all. Way to go gang, and so excited to see what 2020 brings for this group of stars!\n\n77#Expert Guides|Thank you for guiding our teams through a fantastic planning session yesterday.  It was engaging, collaborative and fun.  As a result, we were able to ideate and let our creative juices flow.  I was particularly impressed with your approach to the session.  You constantly had the big picture in mind and guided the team to many important discoveries.  Thank you for using this innovative approach and for rallying the team around shared priorities for 2020.\n\n78#Wonder Woman and She Ra have competition!|Jill and Pam- Thank you so much for bringing us together today to share what you learned and walk us through an exercise that will enable us to be more successful as Marketers! Your willingness to share and maintain transparency makes you both GREAT leaders! I know I don‚Äôt speak for myself when I say ‚ÄúThank You‚Äù for allowing us to be a part of something amazing! If She Ra and Wonder Woman ever joined force they‚Äôd have some serious competition!\n\n79#Cheers to you!!|Pam and Jill - Just wanted to take a moment to TOAST!! to the two of you for an excellent, productive, and super well-run planning meeting yesterday afternoon. The entire team was extremely engaged and collaboration was off the chain. We put our heads together, we were respectful but critical of ourselves, and we came up with some truly innovative ideas that will shape our marketing plans for 2020. I am truly inspired by the teamwork you both showed in leading the meeting together as well. Thanks so much for an excellent afternoon! Looking forward to our top 3 priorities for the year!\n\n80#Bite-sized marketing updates, Buffet-sized results|Great job all on your collective sharings and updates during our full marketing team meeting this week. There is so much goodness happening in marketing right now and each of you showcased the strategic thinking, approach, and results in a very concise way. And...you also stayed on time! This shows how each of you respect each other and the full marketing team. It also ensured that everyone had an opportunity to share their work and create greater alignment across the entire group.  Thank you!\n\n81#Co-creating Great CX is a Team Sport!|Dear Team, I am so grateful to be able to call upon this amazing group of people! You were each willing to invest an entire day to thinking through the customer lens as part of our journey mapping workshop.   To say that I am impressed with the progress we made is an understatement.  We now have 4 draft journey maps - current and dream state for two incredibly important customer types, the End User and Buyer! Thank you for your contribution, energy and excitement about what we are seeking to do and the impact this can have on our business goals!  As we shared, CX is owned by all humans at Workhuman and this team showed so much commitment to CX and excitement around the potential that exists that if this is an indicator of how the rest of the company will feel, it makes me even more excited about how fast we can move our CX from current state to intentional & differentiated!!! Thank you, thank you, thank you!!!  You guys ROCK!\n\n82#All of the presentation & communication wisdom|Many thanks to this group for being involved in the development and setup of the Social Media Workshop presentations! This includes advice on format delivery, timing, content, and communication plan. With participation for each workshop between 30-40 people X 9 workshops, we were successful in \"marketing\" our own event.\n\n83#Suggestion box|Pam- Thank you so much for listening to an unorganized, unfiltered team at what was suppose to be a 2020 planning meeting. You took amazing notes, but most importantly, you took action on them. As I left to grab lunch (thank you btw) I saw you meeting with cross functional teams to maximize our efforts as a company. You worked your way down the list over the last 2 days making our challenges a priority. Thanks for making us feel heard and our concerns a priority. You are an amazing manager! Thank you!\n\n84#Vertical Demo's that are sure to WOW!!|Pam, Maureen, Kelli, Brian and Dan ‚Äì I want to express my gratitude for the work you‚Äôre doing on the vertical demo project.  Developing ‚Äúcustom‚Äù sites for the major vertical markets we pursue is certainly not an easy task ‚Äì you need to focus on brand, infrastructure, setting up users, refreshing the system in a systematic way‚Ä¶the list of to-do‚Äôs to make this happen is certainly a tall order.  But the outcome to date is awesome and having access to a variety of brands that we can showcase in presentations depending on the customer will help us to highlight the flexibility of our platform and differentiate our offering.  Thank you so much for digging into this project and bringing it to life.\n\n85#Setting expectations|Pam, I wanted to take the time to thank you for setting up two very productive meetings. When looped into the 'mapping moments' project by Alice, you took the time to meet with me to catch up on the work I've done thus far on the project. You set expectations from the start of the meeting, listened to all of my updates, and my pitch for using a digital tool. As we wrapped up the meeting, you helped to set-up a timeline and next steps. I really appreciate all of your guidance, and ability to officiate an incredibly productive and actionable meeting.\n\n86#There's no \"I\" in this team|I am so proud to be a member of this team, everyone was so selfless during my paternity leave. I received so many nice texts to check in on my family and ensure that all of my projects stayed on track. The support didn't stop there, from travelling to Washington to help with TOWL and the West QBR, to shipping out crates, preparing for future events, and sending out communications. Pam, Amanda, Krista and Jill, thank you again for everything that you have done. I truly appreciate it, best team ever!!\n\n87#Internship Program Advocate|Pam - thank you so much for your recent help in getting Marketing managers on board for the 2020 Internship Program!  When you heard that I hadn't received too much internal interest, you quickly sent a note out to the managers in Marketing to advocate for the internship program!  Thank you so much for sharing your success story with them.  Since then, we have definitely received more interest within Marketing!  You're a great Recruiting Partner!\n\n88#Successful Kick-off|Pam - Thank you so much for recently taking the time to kick off your team's newest search, Field Marketing Specialist!  We have kicked off new searches before, but we did it differently this time.  Thank you so much for the deep dive into how this role will fit into your team, the responsibilities, and the interview process.  Thank you for your thoughtful breakdown of what each interviewer will be focusing on.  I cannot wait to find your newest team member.  Thanks, Pam!\n\n89#I understand!|Pam- You always know what to say when you get an email from me that‚Äôs lengthy and consists of words like ‚ÄúI feel strongly‚Äù or ‚ÄúI can‚Äôt control my daggers‚Äù. I always feel listened to and heard. We laugh about it the next day and move on to our daily business. I appreciate that I can openly discuss these challenges with you. Thanks for being an awesome mentor! Ps there was no wine used in the making of this moment lol\n\n90#Modernizing demand gen|Jill, Pam, and Matt - I wanted to commend all of your work, passion, and focus around modernizing our demand gen strategy and approach. The three of you have worked diligently over the past couple of months building out the strategy and the how we do it at Workhuman. The meeting with Chris was a great one and it's exactly the type of partnership and future-oriented discussion needed. The marketing world has changed. We have an enormous opportunity to modernize our approach to move from an inquiry model to one that not only targets the right future customers but also drives new demand (and wins at a higher rates due to it being the right opportunity with the right level of investment).  Your efforts make it quite clear how much each of you care about our business opportunity ahead and continuing to elevate how marketing can partner with sales. Thank you!\n\n91#Time is valuable!|Pam - Time is not cheep.  You had a very busy day but you still allowed time for this guy.  I know i ask a lot of crazy questions and but you answered everyone with respect and understanding.  Your knowledge is invaluable to my learning process.  Thank you for your help and teamwork along the way.  It is so appreciated.\n\n92#Takes a village|Team- Took 3 months, numerous meetings and iterations, but we have landed in a great place, with a project we can all be proud of, the new and improved Hello Box! An amazing mentor told me I should be proud of the work I produce and if not proud, to take the time needed to produce excellence...I believe we‚Äôve done that! This is seriously epic and we have all you to thank for that:) So excited to start sending theses Hello Boxes and Folders our to key prospects!! Thank you all for your hard work!!\n\n93#Love the challenge|Pam- You always find ways to challenge me, even if it makes me extremely uncomfortable. There‚Äôs even a lesson in that for me...nothing like agreeing to disagree first thing in the morning! I‚Äôm lucky to have such a great manager who pushes me out of my comfort zone and encourages me to produce the best work, even if it takes longer than I‚Äôd like;)\n\n94#Covering while I was out|Pam and Ryan- Thank you for covering while I was moving into my new house last week! Ryan- you sent out multiple direct mail items and customized messages with little guidance. You worked in a critical presentation with lots and lots of commentary. Pam- You kept the HB on track and moving along so the final product is amazing! Thank you both so much for being amazing!\n\n95#A sweet first day back|Thank you guys so much for keeping me abreast of all the happenings around here while I was out on maternity leave, and for a super sweet first day back in the office. Coming in today to donuts, Night Shift, and pretty flowers on my desk put a huge smile on my face and I really can‚Äôt say enough about how much it meant to get a surprise like that on my first day back. Jeff  - I am already so impressed with the great work you are doing and am looking forward to digging into it all with you! Thanks again for a great first day and your help with the transition!\n\n96#Breakout Support|Thanks to you all for helping facilitate the \"Differentiators\" breakout.  Each of you stepped in to support this activity and make it meaningful for your team members.  This year's Boot Camp was truly a team effort and I appreciate your contribution.\n\n97#Putting the Magic on Paper!|Pam, you have been absolutely amazing taking all of the ideas we have tossed around in regards to Demand Gen 2.0 and making them real on paper; from capturing notes, to building out PowerPoint decks. Working with you on this initiative has been my favorite project over the last few months. So excited to share more ideas (and laughs!) over the course of the second half, we got this!\n\n98#A meaningful Pride|Pam - a very overdue thank you for sending a really impactful article about Pride my way at the start of this month. It touched on a really prevalent topic in the corporate world ‚Äì that companies need to be careful to extend Pride beyond marketing efforts, because it is SO much MORE than that. Your article inspired us to take a closer look at our efforts, and add some really meaningful pieces to our 2019 Pride plan. Thank you!\n\n99#Great Growth Hacking Session|Pam - Great job in bringing in new perspectives and ideas to the Workhuman Cloud for Teams work and more. Your brought in a former colleague of yours - Sean Ellis - for a growth hacking workshop.  While I was only there for the first half, it was a great session!  Our opportunity ahead is incredible - but to truly maximize it, we need to continually challenge our thinking, mindset, and approach (And of course, test, test, test, and test). Training sessions like this one are a great way to do just that.  Excellent work in leveraging your network!\n\n100#Agenda at a Glance|Or, agenda in a moment.  Thanks all for coming up with a great overview of the important projects happening in Marketing, with just a little notice.  It was not only great to hear about the wonderful work happening in Marketing, but to see you all present it all so beautifully.  I am grateful for the talented team of colleagues we have at the helm and in support of all of these initiatives.  Thank you!\n\n101#HIRED!|Pam, congratulations on your newest hire!  This was the first time we had worked together on a search, and boy was it a successful one!  From kick-off, to phone screens, to interviews and feedback sessions.  Thank you for your help and advice along the way.  I am so excited for Mark to be joining your team soon - I am confident that he will do great things!\n\n102#Strategic Experience Mapping Workshops|A big thanks to all of you for coming to the Experience Mapping Workshops ready to share ideas of how we can use WH to help achieve our company goals. It was fantastic to see how aligned everyone is! Your time and dedication will he