esponse to this project and for living our value of 'Respect for Urgency.'  Great job everyone.\n\n145#Let's DO IT!|Thank you all for taking time out of your busy day to brainstorm ideas on the best approach for winning Nike. James and Michael - You walked us through the entire RFP process to help us understand exactly how our audience will be digesting the information and the best approach for getting the message across to the team in the right area. James ,you even took it a step further and helped draft out a script. Jess and Pam - Your marketing expertise and leadership helped to ensure we were asking the right questions and taking the best approach to stand out against our competitors. I am excited to see the final results. All of you showed true dedication to help ensure this project is a success! Thank you all!\n\n146#Great brainstorm|Pam - I wanted to say thank you for organizing a great brainstorming session earlier this week for WorkHuman 2019 promotional planning. You heard as I did, many of us expressing thoughts and ideas in various meetings leading up to this week and decided to  get us all in a room together to share ideas. The meeting was thoughtfully organized but we still had room to think and collaborate as a team which was wonderful. I am grateful for your leadership and look forward to making some of these ideas come to life!\n\n147#Interview on the fly!|Pam, thank you so much for jumping in and joining a very last minute interview team today! We value your opinion and insight into the marketing/sales collaboration - and greatly appreciate you being so willing to step in this morning to interview our candidate. You are such a team player and ensured a quality candidate experience as the schedule was seamless and your interview of him so well done. Thank you for helping make it a fantastic experience for our candidate and for helping me out in a pinch!\n\n148#Planning Teammates!!!|Pam and Janet, I cannot thank you both enough for your support, br