y to be part of it!\n\n155#An incredible crowd of humans- thank you!|Pam, last summer, before I even arrived at Globoforce, you showed tremendous initiative to take on audience acquisition for WH 2018. This was in addition to more than a full-time job and showed me right away your incredible leadership, commitment, and ability to make sure we got this right.This involved orchestrating a complex effort with your (very small) team across a number of tactics including email, social, account-based marketing, and also program design and tools to empower sales and customer success. All of this is of course is HUGE, but as you did in 2017, you also led the charge on targeting the executive forum audience. Incredible results in partnership with sales and customer success-- 2700+ registrations, 300 exec forum-- incredible growth and under budget! What an accomplishment, congratulations and thank you.\n\n156#Pre-WH Recruiting Hustle!|Team - thank you SO much for taking the time to interview our Visual Designer candidate on such short notice.  Everyone was so quick to respond to the request, and so willing to jump onto the interview team.  Also, during the week before WH?  Check.  Honestly, so awesome of you all.  I know how insanely busy this week is for everyone, and you all helped me make this happen.  I SO appreciate this, as it helps us secure great candidates, and create a great candidate experience.  Thank you all so much!!\n\n157#For Customers... and teamwork|You've stepped up to help us rethink customer marketing at a pivotal time as we expand to new markets and targets with WorkHuman Cloud and look to reframe how the market thinks about their total rewards strategy. We are also facing this little task we call WorkHuman followup to gain the most from our investment with customers in Austin. Thank you for your ideas, energy, and initiative ‚Äîand taking on the challenge in the midst of some of the busiest weeks ever. I'm confident that your experience, leadership, and 