tions and responses to these situations remind me what great leaders you are. Thank you for collaborating and working through this with me.\n\n166#Santa's Little Helpers|Thank you so much for getting mine and Brian's SMB christmas \"Thank You Baskets\" out. I asked and you delivered. True teamwork and our clients are really going to appreciate the extra touch. For the business and references they have continued to give us over the year. Thank you !!!!\n\n167#Leading the way!|Pam, there are so many things this award could cover, and I am not even sure where to begin, but first and foremost thank you for being an excellent colleague, friend and mentor. I love the alignment and strategy we've put in place as a team and your continued support has made it all possible. The team is in a strong position to make great things happen and I look forward to 2018, when we can leverage some great reports to see all the plans and strategies leading to awesome results for the company. You're an awesome leader and I'm lucky to learn from and lean on you! Thanks!\n\n168#Pushing projects forward|Kevin and Pam - thank you for helping me route multiple projects to the right people for approvals over the past few weeks. I appreciate your collaborative efforts with the team to ensure we have the right idea in place to move projects forward and make them as perfect as possible to go out into the world. Support like that truly makes us feel like a team with the same goal. Multiple projects needed a strong push in the right direction and you were a big part of making that happen.\n\n169#'It's all happening!'|Walking out of that fantastic presentation, all I could think of one of my favorite quotes from one of my favorite movies of all time, 'It's all happening!' - Almost Famous. You four put together GREAT out-of-the-box ideas that wowed Janet, Kevin and I. Ideas that we are excited to immediately put into production and get out to market! When there are limited boundaries, you all really shine. We can't wait to see it all in action.\n\n170#A-team|I wanted to give a big shout out to this team for getting together regularly so we can tackle challenges and support the whole team as a united front. I've appreciated the frank discussions and ability to share our points of view in a safe environment bent on making things better for everyone. Staying in step with what other parts of the team are facing helps me gain perspective of the bigger picture and set expectations with my own team so that we can offer better support to everyone's priorities. Our meetings make me feel like there isn't anything we can't accomplish!\n\n171#Lead by Example|Pam, Even though you are extremely busy, you took the time to help me get acclimated - from making sure I was invited to the right meetings, to helping me navigate who was who and our processes, to spending time with me to explain \"everything\" I needed to understand. I would not be this far along if you hadn't taken the time to do that. I'm deeply grateful.\n\n172#What a cast of characters you are!|Thank you so much for your starring role in the Conversations video! It was so much fun working with each of you, sharing lots of laughs and serious faces (on camera of course) for our third Globoforce product video. Thanks for playing in our sandbox, you will forever be immortalized as a key to our success!\n\n173#OOO Calendar|Thank you for using the OOO calendar so Angela and I are equipped to schedule meetings and deadlines. It is a small task that makes a big difference in managing your projects; we appreciate it!\n\n174#Encouraging the conversation|Pam- Thank you got encouraging me to have 2 separate uncomfortable conversations last week. You continue to inspire me daily, this time stepping out of my comfort zone. Without your coaching and mentoring, I would have continued to skirt around some frustrating issues. I appreciate the extra push:)\n\n175#Stepping Up With Continual Energy and Drive|Pam and Anne Marie - over t