n and impact the business.  Dan connected the dots to the content that is so critical to support this strategy.  You both demonstrated an understanding of the business, and the needs of the sales organization.  There was applause (i.e for the new Eaton case study); comments (i.e. \"I now understand what Marketing does\"); and a ton of positive feedback.  Your presentation was engaging as it delivered new ideas, new content and a new structure that is needed to hit the ground running in 2017.  I know how difficult it can be to deliver the presentation 4 times in a row, and you guys were fantastic.  Congrats on a job well done.\n\n199#Truly AWESOME|Pam- Over the last couple of weeks, I have come to you looking for advice and guidance, both work and life related. You are always willing to take 2 seconds out of your day to talk about being a mom, what to stress about and what to let go of. When a daycare mommy blew me and my daughter off for a play date, you told me not to take it personally. When webex is being unresponsive and there are 5 different contacts, you inspire me to be non reactive when I want to give up and find a new vendor. When I come to you looking for strengths during times of weakness you are the spark that guides the way. I couldn't be more grateful and proud to have such an amazing mentor and though I want to be selfish and not share you, I know I speak for the whole team when I say that you are truly awesome!\n\n200#Marketing Hackathon Success|Thank you for making the first-ever Marketing Hackathon such a success! You embodied all our core values and the results were fantastic. The two-week Marketing sprint made us more agile as a team, brought out new ideas empowering every member of the team, and we found new approaches to market ‚Äì ideas that could impact both our marketing approach and our go-to market for opportunities ahead. There was a buzz and vibe around the office that was felt by all your enthusiasm and accomplishment - all the way up the executive chain. Simply put, YOU ROCKED IT! Jess, Jill, and Kevin\n\n201#It's all about quality|Pam, Thank you for always being there to provide guidance on marketing initiatives.  I appreciate how you're always focused on what we can do to advance our marketing strategies and have the most impact on our prospects. I really appreciate that you never settle for \"status quo\" and always push us to think outside the box, and improve our approaches/thinking.  I really enjoy working with you and look forward to continuing to build out new campaigns together.\n\n202#Go Team!|Pam/Kristen - What a great day!  A big shout out to both of you for planing and executing a fantastic team event for the Marketing offsite last week.  After a few extremely challenging months for the Marketing department,  the extended team was so ready for an opportunity to bond with teammates, collaborate with x-functional team members in a super-fun context, and have a real positive experience with one another to pick up the morale.  You successfully planned an experience that was engaging for everyone and relevant in terms of cross pollinating our different departments to achieve success. It was a great reminder that we are all in this together.  Thank you for your creativity and for driving this to happen.  It couldn't have come at a better time.\n\n203#Simply Amazing|Pam- You're eyes catch things that many miss. You're ideas are inspirational. You take projects up a notch.  Everyday you raise the bar and challenge others to do the same. I can't thank you enough for being such a great mentor!\n\n204#Thank you!|Pam, Thank you so much for all of your help lately to ensure all of my projects are moving along and approved. I have been running a lot of different projects and ideas by you and you have been extremely helpful at providing your advice and expertise so that I can move forward and create successful campaigns. You have been a great leader and mentor and I appreciate all of your help and 