nd to have your support.\n\n209#First WorkHuman Regional Forum|Well that's another first accomplished today as we completed our first WorkHuman regional forum in New York City. There was such a lot of prep work went into organizing these events. I truly appreciate the work you did as a team to ensure the Agenda was the right mix of inspiration and action - that we could deliver a unique experience and still ensure social recognition is front of mind. I believe we achieved that mix. There are things we learn from doing anything for the first time which will strengthen the next events. Great job on shaping the space to be more WorkHuman like and on securing great customers and outside speakers. I'd say we have a nice New York WorkHuman community building. Great job everyone\n\n210#Innovate, Learn, Repeat|Pam - Just wanted to give you a quick shot out on the Oracle program! It's been a learning experience for both of us working on this uniquely targeted effort and I think you've done a fabulous job leading it. From planning out the timeline of touch points and deliverables, to explaining the very unique message we needed to send, you always made sure I understood your vision and where we needed to go. I can certainly say I have never worked on a campaign quite like this and it has taught me so much in the few weeks I've spent supporting your effort. Thank you for your leadership, collaboration, and dedication. Very glad to be a part of it.\n\n211#Great work with IBM|Pam and Jen, thank you for organizing and managing an extremely productive marketing meeting with two very influential marketers from IBM.  I appreciate the attention to detail on logistics and meeting agenda as well as your work in putting together our first WorkHuman partnership prospectus. I am very confident we came away with a concrete plan and that we left them motivated to take action. Thank you\n\n212#Sizzling Summer Series|The WorkHuman summer series agenda is hot!! Great work in bringing all compo