d the ideas discussed have given us all great next steps.  This is the type of thought leadership and teamwork I love about Globoforce, all teams and roles coming together to make the most of an opportunity.  I am excited to partner with you all on this as we move forward!  Thanks!\n\n222#Campaign Success|Pam - Congrats on the excellent job you did planning and executing the first phase of the fully integrated Employee Appreciation Day marketing campaign.  Like many recent initiatives, you did not have a lot of runway getting this launched.  However, despite the short timeframe you pulled together many cross-functional stakeholder and lead the virtual team to execute an outstanding example of a multi-touch; multi-media campaign that included media coverage, webinars, emails, blogs, digital ads, newsletter..and more. Early indicators are showing fantastic results.  Kudos to you and the team. I can't wait to see what Phase II has in store.\n\n223#Teamwork!|Anthony, Sarah and Pam,   What a great team we have! Thank you so much for being the main point of contact for the activities I had going on while I was away on vacation. You kept it all going!  Thank you!!\n\n224#Guidance|Thank you Pam for the guidance and mentoring throughout the EAD Campaign and over the last 2 weeks. There was a lot of hard work that went into this campaign and we could not have done it without your leadership! I am so excited to be part of the team:)\n\n225#I have the best team ever!|Kevin, Jess, Pam, Jill, Sarah, Megan -- I wanted to thank each and every one of you for the incredible reminder you collectively gave to me yesterday, which is, how blessed I am to work with the team that surrounds me at Globoforce.  You each reorganized your busy day to lend your helping hands when I needed them the most, and I can't even begin to tell you how much I appreciated that yesterday.  Thank you.\n\n226#Power to the process|Just wanted to give  a shout out about that awesome process meeting! No one loves