ke a true part of this process and we are all eager to see the results.  Thanks for being such a great partner!\n\n237#Great work behind the scenes|Pam Every day I am thrilled to see people on our team being recognized for the great work they do in supporting others members of our company. Many of the activities we work on are very visible to other teams and deserve recognition. However - our marketing programs, events and campaigns would never be successful without the direction and guidance you give your team. The work you are doing right now to build objectives, processes and hire new members of the team are critical for our future success. So while it may not be visible to everyone it is such important work. I see you driving hard each day and am impressed at the workload you are managing. You have a great ability to prioritize and get things done. Keep up the great work\n\n238#Fast track team|I just wanted to give you guys a big thanks for jumping on the GPTW/WorkHuman invitation! We got down to the wire but made our deadline because you were all able to make this job a priority and bring your A-game when we really needed it. Thanks for jumping on it‚ÄìI think it will be a great asset to help promote WorkHuman at the GPTW event as well as give us a structure to build on as we get more info about WorkHuman 2016!\n\n239#Inspired, insightful collaboration|Jess, Pam and Kevin: I want to thank the three of you for collaborating to build the Marketing Department offsite agenda.  You took your personal understanding of the team's needs for information and inspiration and modeled an agenda that served both needs beautifully.  Our team is more engaged, more aligned in our thinking and more inspired in our vision as a result of the agenda you three created, and from all of us, I thank you.\n\n240#Marketing Team Takes Newport|Thank you for organizing an offsite that was thoughtful, well structured, and also lots of fun! I can't wait to see how the insights and stories we 