k you for your help with the customer communication and your content direction was incredible - what value you have brought to every part of the event that you have touched - which is basically the entire event! Kevin, thank you for working on the Ambassador experience and providing input on many areas of the customer evening also.  Kerry, thank you for driving the meet and greets and Pam, thank you for keeping us on track with the i‚Äôs dotted and t‚Äôs crossed across so many areas large and small, your attention to detail is a wonder! Nothing passes you by down to the last detail ‚Äì table tents, name badges, place cards and more.  Anne Marie, Anthony and Jess D, thank you for your help with customer registrations and automated communications! Having your assistance helped provide visibility as we tried to drive recruitment and peace of mind as we implemented the customer communication plan.  Thank you Team!  What a privilege it is to work with such professionals!  I am so excited by what we have created this year and the mind boggles with what we can do next year!  Thank you!\n\n249#Dream Team|If I could wrap all 5 Awards into one recognition I would, but since I cant I choose teamwork. We began this WorkHuman journey together 6 months ago and the results of everyone's hard work, perseverance, dedication, passion and commitment was evident leading up to the conference and definitely throughout the conference. The conference was the most visually appealing I have ever been to. Our content and program was powerful and motivational, our social media outreach was phenomenal, Workhuman central was interactive and provided great networking opportunities. The onsite teamwork shown by the blue team, registration team and all of our greeters was very personal and friendly. I couldn't have been more proud to have such a great group of humans to take this journey with. Thank you to all for making this truly a dream team for me.\n\n250#Reserver Super Star|Hi Pam,  I just want to thank you for all of your help at WorkHuman!  You were always there to help Eric and I get us anything we needed.   Over the past three days we have really gotten to know each other through our shared goal of making Workhuman a massive success.   In my entire career I have never been so proud to work with such an incredible team!  Thank you for all you do and going above and beyond for both Eric and I.\n\n251#Marketing Magic at Workhuman|The conference speaks for itself.  Well done!\n\n252#Stepping up on a moments notice!|Pam I can't thank you enough for jumping in with Bank of America with literally a moments notice.  Asking you to engage them about the upcoming Boston Evanta CHRO conference.  What I thought would be a 5 minute conversation, you engaged them for 20 minutes.  You then proceeded to take time away from dinner to construct a detailed email of the conversation and strategy on next steps.  Feeling like they would be \"overwhelmed\" by Globoforce, you proved them wrong helping bring their guard down.  Your a true team player and I appreciate your sense of Urgency to help \"on a moments notice\".\n\n253#Leadership starts here!|Pam, this was a tough week for me as we wrap up projects leading up to WorkHuman and I nervously anticipate what‚Äôs next. You are the calm leader, able to help me focus and prioritize my scattered list of to-dos. Even when you don‚Äôt have all the answers, you find a way to help me sort things out, step back and focus on the now. Thank you for your leadership and for the wisdom that couldn't have come at a better time.\n\n254#Team work and Onboarding|Hi Pam, I wanted to thank you for helping me gather all the on boarding documentation we have from different areas so I could be prepared to support Marion. We are all being pulled in a million directions and I wanted to thank you for taking time out of your day to be a one stop shop for me. It will help me get Marion up to speed quickly and for that, we both thank you! Anne Marie\